<h2 class="bac"><img class="pclose" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Hide information" title="Hide information">Our Business</h2>
<div>
<h3 class="bac">Summary</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Locations London, Bromley  &amp; Croydon</li>
	<li>On track for a minimum of a 2:1 degree classification (or equivalent) any degree discipline</li>
	<li>Genuine interest in a career within financial markets</li>
	<li>2 year rotational programme</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">Innovation is at the heart of everything we do. Continuous improvement and a desire to remain at the forefront of the world&#39;s financial markets is what makes working at Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Merrill Lynch such an exciting place.</p>
<p class="bac">The primary functions within the GCCIBT  &amp;O business are to provide the technology platforms that support our payment and Wire processes around the world, and the applications that support the operations and services of our International Branches.</p>
<p class="bac">The teams also deliver operational processing and integrated service and fulfillment capabilities to our clients through our Global Wire Operations teams and the International branch network.</p>
<p class="bac">We are looking for ambitious graduates to work with the smartest people at the heart of the financial world. And we mean world. The global nature of our function will allow you the opportunity to work and interact with colleagues across the globe preparing you for an unlimited career in the Bank.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information">Overview</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">Our rotational programme focuses primarily on the Operations side of this business. Teams you could rotate into are:</p>
<h3 class="bac">Fulfillment</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>The Fulfillment team consists of groups of project managers delivering the bank&#39;s end to end cash and treasury management solutions for Large Corporate and FI clients across the Europe and Emerging Markets (ex-Asia) region.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Servicing</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Responsible for managing the day-to-day relationships with our Corporate, FI and Corporate Card clients. Responsible for navigating the bank on our clients&#39; behalf, facilitating ongoing business discussions and for resolving all complex and transactional enquiries relating to cash management</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Operations</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Provides operational support for both Global Product Solutions (GPS) and Global Corporate  &amp; Investment Banking (GCIB) clients, associates are directly responsible for the day to day back office and business operations. Including processing and investigating incoming and outgoing funds transfers for all Bank clients, their clients and internal Bank units globally, along with ensuring the rigorous regulatory requirements are met.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

